IV  6   It is a holiday.  Their father says: 'Oh, it is so pleasant here.'  They are fighting all the time.  Stefan and Kim are sitting in the backseat of the car. What did the father want to convey?
IV  13  When you ask him how it is going he says, 'It couldn't be any better.' Your friend is working on his novel and is not making any progress. What does your friend want to convey?
IV  24  Her brother said, 'I see your revision is going well.' It was the night before her exam and Tilly had read none of the course texts. What did he want to convey?
IV  25  Tony commented, 'Classy outfit.' Barb and Tony went to a high school reunion. Barb was running late and came underdressed. What did Tony want to convey?